{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### **Happiness Score Model**\n","\n","**Why did we build it?**\n","After successfully predicting addiction level, we wanted to explore a more complex target — one where no single feature dominates. Happiness score is influenced by a combination of gaming behavior, social relationships, and health indicators, making it a richer and more challenging prediction problem.\n","\n","**What does it measure?**\n","It predicts each user's happiness score on a numeric scale, based on a mix of behavioral, social, and physical health features — answering the question: \"What makes a gamer happy?\"\n","\n","**Why does it matter?**\n","Because happiness is the ultimate outcome of a balanced lifestyle. Identifying the factors that drive or reduce happiness in the gaming community can help researchers, developers, and health professionals design better interventions and healthier gaming environments."],"metadata":{"nteract":{"transient":{"deleting":false}},"microsoft":{"language":"python","language_group":"synapse_pyspark"}},"id":"ebf1347b-09d1-4667-b6df-b6f22d491b03"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### **Happiness Model Steps:**\n","\n","Cell 1  → Import Libraries (including shap & %pip install shap)\n","\n","Cell 2  → Load Gold Tables\n","\n","Cell 3  → Join Tables\n","\n","Cell 4  → Drop Leakage + Define Target (happiness_score)\n","\n","Cell 5  → Encode Categoricals\n","\n","Cell 6  → EDA: Target Distribution + Top Correlated Features\n","\n","Cell 7  → Train/Test Split + Scale\n","\n","Cell 8  → Train 3 Models (Linear Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost)\n","          with MLflow Tracking\n","\n","Cell 9  → Model Comparison Chart (RMSE, MAE, R²)\n","\n","Cell 10 → Feature Importance (Best Model)\n","\n","Cell 11 → SHAP Values (Full Test Data)\n","\n","Cell 12 → Register Best Model in MLflow Registry"],"metadata":{"nteract":{"transient":{"deleting":false}},"microsoft":{"language":"python","language_group":"synapse_pyspark"}},"id